        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 12:29AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1229 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 6 miles
south of Inola, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Mazie...                          Chouteau...
Wagoner...                        Inola...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
